text: Eupterote asclepiades is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Swinhoe in 1894. It is found in Sundaland. The habitat consist of lowland rainforests, including hill dipterocarp forests. The larvae are polyphagous.The Moths of Borneo ==References== Category:Moths described in 1894 Category:Eupterotinae Category:Moths of Asia
